```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Page xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
       xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
       x:Class="StopwatchApp.StopwatchPage"
       Title="Stopwatch"
       Background="White">

    <Grid>
        <Border Background="#f0f0f0" CornerRadius="10" Padding="20">

            <Label x:Name="StartTimeLabel" Content="00:00:00" Style="{DynamicResource LocalText}"  FontSize="36" HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>

            <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal" Margin="0" VerticalAlignment="Center">
                <Button x:Name="StartButton" Content="Start" Width="80" Height="35" Margin="0,0,10,0" Click="StartButton_Click"/>
                <Button x:Name="StopButton" Content="Stop" Width="80" Height="35" Margin="0,0,10,0" Click="StopButton_Click" Visibility="Collapsed"/>
                <Button x:Name="ResetButton" Content="Reset" Width="80" Height="35" Margin="0,0,10,0" Click="ResetButton_Click" Visibility="Collapsed"/>
            </StackPanel>


            <Label x:Name="LapTimeLabel" Content="Lap Time: 00:00:00" Style="{DynamicResource LocalText}"  FontSize="20" HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="0, 20, 0, 0"/>
            <TextBox x:Name="LapTimeTextBox" Text="00:00:00" Style="{DynamicResource LocalText}" ReadOnly="True" HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="0,0,0,20"/>

        </Border>
    </Grid>
</Page>
```

**Explanation:**

* **`<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>`**:  XML declaration.
* **`<Page ...>`**:  Defines the XAML page.
    * `xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"`:  Specifies the namespaces needed.  This is essential!
    * `xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"`:  For XAML extension methods like `x:Name`.
    * `x:Class="StopwatchApp.StopwatchPage"`:  Links this page to your C# class (replace `StopwatchApp` with your actual namespace).
    * `Title="Stopwatch"`: Sets the title of the page.
    * `Background="White"`: Sets the background color.
* **`<Grid ...>`**:  The main container for the page layout.
* **`<Border ...>`**:  Provides a bordered area for better appearance.
    * `Background="#f0f0f0"`:  Light gray background color.
    *  `CornerRadius="10"`: Adds rounded corners.
    * `Padding="20"`: Adds padding around the content inside the border.
* **`<Label x:Name="StartTimeLabel" ...>`**:  Displays the current elapsed time.
    * `x:Name="StartTimeLabel"`:  Assigns the name "StartTimeLabel" to this label, allowing you to access it in your C# code.
    * `Content="00:00:00"`:  Initial text displayed.
    * `Style="{DynamicResource LocalText}"`:  Applies a localized text style (useful for handling different languages).  You'll need to define a `LocalText` style in your application's resource dictionary.
    * `FontSize="36"`:  Sets the font size.
    * `HorizontalAlignment="Center"`: Centers the label horizontally.
* **`<StackPanel ...>`**:  Arranges the buttons horizontally.
    * `Orientation="Horizontal"`:  Arranges the elements horizontally.
    * `Margin="0"`: Removes any default margins.
    * `VerticalAlignment="Center"`: Centers the stack panel vertically.
* **`<Button ...>`**:  Creates the buttons.
    * `x:Name="StartButton"`:  Assigns the name "StartButton" for access in code.
    * `Content="Start"`:  Button text.
    * `Width="80"` and `Height="35"`:  Set the button size.
    * `Margin="0,0,10,0"`: Sets the horizontal margins.
    * `Click="StartButton_Click"`:  Specifies the C# event handler function to call when the button is clicked.
    * `Visibility="Collapsed"`: Initially hides the "Stop" and "Reset" buttons. They'll be shown when the "Start" button is clicked and hidden when the "Stop" button is clicked.
* **`<Label x:Name="LapTimeLabel" ...>`**: Displays the lap time.
* **`<TextBox x:Name="LapTimeTextBox" ...>`**: Displays the lap time as a read-only text box.
    * `ReadOnly="True"`:  Prevents the user from directly editing the lap time.
* **`Style="{DynamicResource LocalText}"`**: Applying a localized text style, for proper language support.  You'll need to define a `LocalText` style in your App.xaml or another resource dictionary.  Here's an example:

```xml
<Style x:Key="LocalText"  Panel.ZOrder = "0">
    <TextBlock FontWeight="Normal" FontSize="12" />
</Style>
```

**To use this XAML:**

1.  **Create a WPF project (or a project that uses XAML and C#).**
2.  **Add a new Page to your project.**
3.  **Paste the XAML code into the `Page.xaml` file.**
4.  **Implement the button click handlers in your C# code (e.g., in the `StopwatchPage.xaml.cs` file).**  You'll need to manage the stopwatch timer, start/stop/reset logic, and update the labels and text box.

**C# Code Example (StopwatchPage.xaml.cs):**

```csharp
using System;
using System.Threading;
using System.Windows;
using System.Windows.Controls;

namespace StopwatchApp
{
    public partial class StopwatchPage : Page
    {
        private Stopwatch stopwatch;
        private bool isRunning;

        public StopwatchPage()
        {
            InitializeComponent();
            stopwatch = new Stopwatch();
            isRunning = false;
        }

        private void StartButton_Click(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
        {
            if (!isRunning)
            {
                stopwatch.Start();
                isRunning = true;
                StartButton.Visibility = Visibility.Hidden;
                StopButton.Visibility = Visibility.Visible;
                ResetButton.Visibility = Visibility.Visible;
            }
        }

        private void StopButton_Click(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
        {
            if (isRunning)
            {
                stopwatch.Stop();
                isRunning = false;
                StartButton.Visibility = Visibility.Visible;
                StopButton.Visibility = Visibility.Hidden;
                ResetButton.Visibility = Visibility.Visible;
            }
        }

        private void ResetButton_Click(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
        {
            stopwatch.Reset();
            isRunning = false;
            StartButton.Visibility = Visibility.Visible;
            StopButton.Visibility = Visibility.Hidden;
            ResetButton.Visibility = Visibility.Hidden;
            StartTimeLabel.Content = "00:00:00";
            LapTimeLabel.Content = "Lap Time: 00:00:00";
            LapTimeTextBox.Text = "00:00:00";
        }
    }
}
```

**Important Considerations:**

* **Error Handling:** Add error handling (e.g., `try-catch` blocks) in your C# code to handle exceptions that might occur during stopwatch operation.
* **Threading:**  For a smooth user experience, perform the time updates on a separate thread (e.g., using `Dispatcher.Invoke` if you are updating UI elements from a different thread).  The above example doesn't include threading for simplicity.
* **User Experience:**  Consider adding features like lap timing, displaying intervals, and setting the stopwatch duration.
* **Localization:**  Using `DynamicResource`  and defining a localized style is important for making your application available in multiple languages.
* **Resource Dictionary:**  Put your `LocalText` style (and any other styles or resources) in a resource dictionary (e.g., `App.xaml` or a custom resource dictionary).

