Important Considerations and Further Enhancements:

* **Security (CORS):**  One of the biggest challenges with iframes is Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS).  If the content in the iframe is hosted on a different domain than your Next.js application, the server hosting that content *must* allow your domain to access it through CORS.  If CORS is not configured correctly, the browser will block the iframe from loading, and you'll likely see an error message in the console.  This is usually the most common cause of iframe problems.  The server hosting the iframe content needs to have the appropriate `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header.
